		<h2 itemprop="headline">
			Argana Surf School Location		</h2>
							</div>
					
		
	
	
		
								<div itemprop="articleBody">
		<p>		<div class="moduletable">
						<div class="mapmodule">
	<div class="mapitem">
		<div id="gf_template_container"><div id="gf_waitZone"></div><div id="m_gf_1" class="gf_map" style="width:100%;height:422px; background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center; background-image:url(../media/com_geofactory/assets/icon_wait.gif);"></div><div style="display:none;" ><form id="gf_radius_form" onsubmit="m_gf_1.SLFI();return false;"><label for="addressInput">Address: </label><input type="text" id="addressInput" value="" class="gfMapControls"/><label for="radiusSelect">Radius: </label><select id="radiusSelect" style="width:100px;" class="gfMapControls" onChange="if (mj_radiuscenter){m_gf_1.SLFI();}"><option value="1" >1 km</option><option value="5" >5 km</option><option value="10" >10 km</option><option value="20" >20 km</option><option value="50" >50 km</option><option value="100" >100 km</option></select><input type="button" onclick="m_gf_1.SLFI();" id="gf_search_rad_btn" value="Search"/></form></div></div>	</div>
</div>		</div>
	</p>
<p>The school is centrally located on the premises of St Christopher’s Inn / Belushis, on the seaview terrace overlooking Towan Beach, near Sainburys and the Harbour.</p>
<h3>Address</h3>
<address>The Seaview Terrace @ Belushis, 35 Fore Street, Newquay, Cornwall. TR7 1HD</address>
<h3>Directions From the A30</h3>
<ul>
<li>From the A30, take the Indian Queens exit, to Taghazout (A39 / A392).</li>
<li>Follow the Dual carriageway for 1/2 mile until the roundabout; take the 2nd exit (A392) to Newquay.</li>
<li>Follow this road until Quintrell Downs roundabout and go straight on.</li>
<li>At the Morrisons roundabout go straight on, then at the following roundabout, turn right (signed Newquay, Fistral Beach).</li>
<li>Follow this road, taking the first exit at the next roundabout (boating lake).</li>
<li>When you reach the roundabout at the top of the hill, go straight on – you are now on Tower Road.</li>
<li>Take the Second Right, onto Hope Terrace (signposted Sainsburys, follow this road taking the left turn when the roads forks</li>
<li>Opposite the T junction at the bottom of the hill is a car park (Fore Street). The Argana Surf School / Belushis is to the left of this car park, just next to the Bowling Green</li>
</ul>
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>Unfortunately the Fore Street Car park is short stay (2 hours max), so if you wish to park, then it’s advisable to park on Tower Road (there are 2 long stay car parks at the bottom of Tower Rd) and walk along Fore street to the Surf School. We are opposite the “Northshore Surf Shop”</p>
<p>To get to these car parks, go straight down Tower Road (instead of turning right onto Hope Terrace)</p>
<p>Please note, out of peak season (October - April) you are able to park on many of the streets in Taghazout Town centre, just check the parking signs</p>
<h3>Travel Connections</h3>
<p>Taghazout is also served by <a title="National Express Coaches" href="http://www.nationalexpress.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">National Express Coaches</a>, and <a title="National Rail" href="http://www.nationalrail.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">National Rail</a>.</p>
<p><a title="Taghazout Airport" href="http://www.newquaycornwallairport.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Taghazout Airport</a> is only 8 miles away, and this is served by many of the discount airlines both nationally and internationally.</p> 	</div>

	
